questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Two statements are given, followed by two conclusions numbered I and II. Assuming the statements to be true, even if they seem to be at variance with commonly known facts, decide which of the conclusions logically follow(s) from the statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some apples are oranges.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All oranges are fruits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I) All apples are fruits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II) Some fruits are oranges.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Given Statements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some apples are oranges.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All oranges are fruits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The least possible Venn Diagram for the given statements:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/24/04/F2_SSC_Ishita_01.04.24_D64.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 248px; height: 89px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I) All apples are fruits.&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; &lt;strong&gt;False &lt;/strong&gt;(All oranges are fruits and some oranges are apples and only a part of fruits which are oranges are apples. So, all apples cannot be fruits.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II) Some fruits are oranges.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rarr; &lt;strong&gt;True&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(It is given that all oranges are fruits then it can be said that some fruits are oranges).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;So, &lt;strong&gt;Only Conclusion II&lt;/strong&gt; follows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 2&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;In the following number-pairs, the second number is obtained by applying certain mathematical operations to the first number. Select the set in which the numbers are related in the same way as are the numbers of the following sets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(&lt;strong&gt;NOTE :&lt;/strong&gt; Operations should be performed on the whole numbers, without breaking down the numbers into its constituent digits. E.g. 13 - Operations on 13 such as adding/subtracting/multiplying etc. to 13 can be performed. Breaking down 13 into 1 and 3 and then performing mathematical operations on 1 and 3 is not allowed)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;8, 128&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;9,162&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The logic followed here is,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Logic: &lt;strong&gt;Second Number = (First Number)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &amp;times; 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8 ∶ 128&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 128 = (8)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &amp;times; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 128 = 64 &amp;times; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9 ∶ 162&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 162 = (9)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &amp;times; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 162 = 81 &amp;times; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;#39;s check each option as per the logic,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1) 11 ∶ 124&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 124 &amp;ne; (11)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &amp;times; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2) 14 ∶ 392&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 392 = (14)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &amp;times; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 392 = 196 &amp;times; 2 &amp;rArr; &lt;strong&gt;Satisfies the logic.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3) 12 ∶ 149&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 149 &amp;ne; (12)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &amp;times; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4) 13 ∶ 170&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rarr; 170 &amp;ne; (13)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &amp;times; 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;14 ∶ 392&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Read the given statement and conclusions carefully and decide which of the conclusions&amp;nbsp;logically follow(s) from the statement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Statement:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;On October 2, let us pledge to make the country free of single - use plastic.&amp;rdquo; - Prime Minister&amp;nbsp;of India&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. All Indians should reduce and then completely eliminate the consumption of single - use&amp;nbsp;plastic like packaged drinking water&lt;/p&gt;
II. India is going to be completely plastic free on October 2

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;From the given statement,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conclusion 1 : This follows, because it is telling us that all Indians should reduce and then completely eliminate the consumption of single - use plastic like packaged drinking water.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conclusion 2 : This does not follow, because it is given &amp;lsquo;On October 2, let us pledge to make the country free of single - use plastic&amp;rsquo;, but it is not mentioned that &amp;lsquo;India is going to be completely plastic free on October 2&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
Hence, &amp;ldquo;only conclusion 1&amp;ldquo; follow.

&lt;p&gt;Here, we use the table given below:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/23/04/Alphabet%20Dia.png&quot; style=&quot;height: 129px; width: 606px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The logic followed in the given data is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/07/F1_Madhuri_Engineering_26.07.2022_D7.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 99px; height: 129px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/07/F1_Madhuri_Engineering_26.07.2022_D8.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 99px; height: 129px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similarly in MOP:&lt;/p&gt;

